{"title":"Esker Cycles releases Steel Version of Lorax Dropbar MTB & Smokey Hardtail","link":"https://bikerumor.com/esker-cycles-steel-lorax-dropbar-mtb-smokey-hardtail/","date":1721132638000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/DSC08285-2-Large.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" alt=\"(Photos / Esker Cycles)\" /></p>\n<p>Hot on the heels of the release of the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/the-new-aggressive-smokey-ti-broadens-esker-cycles-hardtail-lineup/\" target=\"_blank\">Smokey</a> and <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/esker-lorax-ti-go-everywhere-drop-bar-mountain-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">Lorax</a> titanium versions, Esker is following up with a different kind of metal. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Smokey and Lorax are once again the newest members of the Esker family, but this time they arrive with steel frames that offer the durability and ease of maintenance that Esker prioritizes in its line. Both sport external cable routing, a threaded bottom bracket, and a 44mm head tube. They also carry a plethora of water bottles and accessory attachment points to facilitate big, backcountry adventures.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>“<em>We like to name our bikes after iconic defenders of wild spaces and the Smokey and Lorax are no exception. We like to imagine that if</em> <em>the legendary bear and mustachioed creature from our youth rode a mountain bike, these would be it</em>“. – Tim Krueger, Owner of Esker Cycles</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Lorax Steel</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-on-gravel-e1721066402753.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"565\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-on-gravel-e1721066402753.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Lorax Steel Lorax on gravel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-on-gravel-e1721066402753.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-on-gravel-e1721066402753-297x131.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-on-gravel-e1721066402753-120x53.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-on-gravel-e1721066402753-768x339.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo / Esker Cyles)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Lorax might be the ideal, do anything, drop bar mountain bike. It utilizes the same quad-butted steel tubing as the Hayduke hardtail. This gives it a supple, yet durable ride.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-downtube-logo.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-downtube-logo.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-downtube-logo.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-downtube-logo-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-downtube-logo-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-downtube-logo-768x768.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-toptube-logo.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-toptube-logo.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Lorax Steel toptube logo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-toptube-logo.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-toptube-logo-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-toptube-logo-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-toptube-logo-768x768.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-WTC-carbon-fork.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-WTC-carbon-fork.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Lorax Steel WTC carbon fork\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-WTC-carbon-fork.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-WTC-carbon-fork-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-WTC-carbon-fork-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-WTC-carbon-fork-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-WTC-carbon-fork-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-WTC-carbon-fork-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Seuss-tree.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Seuss-tree.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Lorax Steel Seuss tree\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Seuss-tree.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Seuss-tree-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Seuss-tree-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Seuss-tree-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Seuss-tree-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Seuss-tree-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-XT-cranks.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-XT-cranks.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Lorax Steel XT cranks\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-XT-cranks.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-XT-cranks-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-XT-cranks-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-XT-cranks-768x768.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-full-bike-blue.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-full-bike-blue.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Lorax Steel full bike blue\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-full-bike-blue.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-full-bike-blue-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-full-bike-blue-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-full-bike-blue-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-full-bike-blue-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-full-bike-blue-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-framset-in-Burlap.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"906\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-framset-in-Burlap.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Lorax Steel framset in Burlap\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-framset-in-Burlap.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-framset-in-Burlap-297x210.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-framset-in-Burlap-120x85.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-framset-in-Burlap-768x544.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Lorax is available as a complete bike or a frameset with a Wolf Tooth Lithic Carbon Mountain fork that’s painted to match. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>The Lorax Geo</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-Geo.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"643\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-Geo.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Lorax Steel Lorax Geo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-Geo.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-Geo-297x149.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-Geo-120x60.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-Geo-768x386.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-Geo-chart.jpg\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"401\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-Geo-chart.jpg\" alt=\"Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-Geo-chart.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-Geo-chart.jpg 1024w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-Geo-chart-297x116.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-Geo-chart-120x47.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Lorax-Steel-Lorax-Geo-chart-768x301.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Lorax Retail &amp; Key Features</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: Starting at $1600 (frame &amp; fork painted to match)<br />Complete builds: Starting at $3000 (with a cornucopia of upgrade options)</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Mountain bike fit and feel. Designed with shorter stems and wider handlebars in mind for more control and better handling in rough terrain.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Optimized geometry for a rigid fork with a 495mm axle to crown, or a 120mm suspension fork.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Mountain bike spacing standards: 73mm BSA bottom bracket, Boost spacing, 44mm head tube, 31.6 seat tube.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Dropper compatible, with internal routing at the seat tube.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Designed around a 29 x 2.2” tire with clearance for up to a 29 x 2.6”</li>\n\n\n\n<li>15 attachment points + rack/fender mounts. Directly mount a top tube bag plus 3-pack mounts on both the bottom and top of your downtube.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Custom drawn externally tapered, seamless, quadruple butted, heat treated 4130 DOM Chromoly tubeset that is specific to each frame size.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Adjustable UDH Portage Dropout with a new Flat Mount version for the Lorax. Dial in your chainstay length or run as a singlespeed.</li>\n\n\n\n<li> Painted-to-match <a href=\"https://www.wolftoothcomponents.com/collections/all-products/products/lithic-carbon-mountain-fork\" target=\"_blank\">Wolf Tooth Lithic Carbon Mountain fork </a>with adjustable offset and 3-pack mounts.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Colors: Saguaro (Metallic Green), Burlap (Tan), Dusk (Dark Blue)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Smokey Steel</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Smokey-Steel-full-bike-on-gravel-e1721067504964.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Smokey-Steel-full-bike-on-gravel-e1721067504964.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Smokey Steel full bike on gravel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Smokey-Steel-full-bike-on-gravel-e1721067504964.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Smokey-Steel-full-bike-on-gravel-e1721067504964-297x132.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Smokey-Steel-full-bike-on-gravel-e1721067504964-120x53.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Smokey-Steel-full-bike-on-gravel-e1721067504964-768x341.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Smokey is the most aggressive hardtail in the Esker line. It has the same features as the titanium counterpart. It’s built with a robust double-butted, heat-treated 4130 chromoly DOM tubeset. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Smokey-Steel-Smokeys-shovel.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Smokey-Steel-Smokeys-shovel.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Smokey Steel Smokeys shovel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Smokey-Steel-Smokeys-shovel.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Smokey-Steel-Smokeys-shovel-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Smokey-Steel-Smokeys-shovel-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Smokey-Steel-Smokeys-shovel-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Smokey-Steel-Smokeys-shovel-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Smokey-Steel-Smokeys-shovel-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-Smokey-Steel-top-tube-logo.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Esker-Cycles-S